WEBVTT

00:04.352 --> 00:04.526
.

00:04.569 --> 00:07.442
[intense music]

00:07.485 --> 00:08.878
- I'm looking for the owner
of that Mustang.

00:08.921 --> 00:11.098
- Haven't seen him.
- How about you, little girl?

00:11.141 --> 00:12.838
- My sister doesn't speak.

00:12.882 --> 00:16.103
- My back needs to be drained.
Or I may never walk again.

00:16.146 --> 00:18.148
- Guys,
I need to have an anesthetic,

00:18.192 --> 00:19.497
something to numb the pain.

00:19.541 --> 00:21.282
- Ta-da--there's
a drug dealer down here.

00:21.325 --> 00:23.893
- Heroin's an opiate.
It's made from morphine.

00:23.936 --> 00:25.373
Are you ready to do this?

00:25.416 --> 00:27.723
- The day of the accident,
I wasn't working late.

00:27.766 --> 00:30.508
I was with someone.
- Levi Delgado.

00:30.552 --> 00:32.119
He was one
of my closest friends.

00:32.162 --> 00:34.643
Do you still love her?
- Gavin, I'm sorry.

00:34.686 --> 00:37.341
- When you find Eve,
I need you to give her this.

00:38.777 --> 00:41.345
You bring my family home.
- You got my word.

00:41.389 --> 00:43.869
[alarm beeping]
Approaching sinkhole!

00:43.913 --> 00:45.654
[indistinct shouting]

00:47.003 --> 00:48.352
- Levi!

00:50.137 --> 00:53.227
[fire crackling,
insects chirping]

00:54.793 --> 00:57.144
- Look at that sky.

00:57.187 --> 01:00.060
Look, you see Mars,
that red star?

01:00.103 --> 01:01.278
- Yeah.
- Okay, that was named

01:01.322 --> 01:03.628
after the Roman god of war.

01:03.672 --> 01:05.065
The thing is,
he won't be written about

01:05.108 --> 01:06.979
for the next 9,000 years.

01:07.023 --> 01:09.286
- So?
- So?

01:09.330 --> 01:13.073
None of these planets
have been named yet, man.

01:13.116 --> 01:15.118
You want your own planet?

01:15.162 --> 01:19.731
From this day forward, Mars
shall be known as Planet Josh.

01:21.342 --> 01:23.866
- You ever consider cutting
back on the weed intake?

01:23.909 --> 01:27.043
- Guys, guys!
We have a serious problem.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.132
It's Tony, he's hurt.

01:29.176 --> 01:30.394
I need the heroin
to do another surgery.

01:30.438 --> 01:32.788
- This is so not good.

01:33.832 --> 01:36.879
- [laughs]
- You're messing with us?

01:36.922 --> 01:39.011
- You should see the look
on your faces right now.

01:39.055 --> 01:40.926
- Yeah, very funny.
Not that we would have been

01:40.970 --> 01:42.406
able to help him anyway.

01:42.450 --> 01:43.538
- What do you mean by that?

01:43.581 --> 01:45.496
- I buried the drugs
in the woods.

01:45.540 --> 01:47.933
- Why did you do that?
- Uh, because it's heroin.

01:47.977 --> 01:49.065
- What if the person that it

01:49.109 --> 01:50.588
belongs to comes looking
for it?

01:50.632 --> 01:52.808
- Okay, well, they haven't
come looking for it yet.

01:52.851 --> 01:54.766
So that tells me either
they didn't survive the fall

01:54.810 --> 01:56.203
or they were never down here
in the first place.

01:56.246 --> 01:58.118
Look, I'm a paranoid person
by nature.

01:58.161 --> 02:00.555
It's me.
And I'm not worried about this.

02:00.598 --> 02:01.947
Relax.

02:01.991 --> 02:04.950
[ominous music]

02:04.994 --> 02:11.827
♪

02:13.350 --> 02:15.483
- What the hell did you do
with my bag?

02:18.616 --> 02:21.097
- I didn't take your stash.

02:21.141 --> 02:23.447
But even if I did,
what good is it to you anyway?

02:23.491 --> 02:25.797
Look around.
There aren't any buyers here.

02:25.841 --> 02:28.191
- I swear,
you don't put it back

02:28.235 --> 02:31.151
by the end of the day--
- You'll what?

02:31.194 --> 02:33.631
You'll kill me?

02:33.675 --> 02:35.851
- Wouldn't be a first
for this family.

02:46.514 --> 02:50.300
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:50.344 --> 02:52.781
Looks like
you're doing better.

02:52.824 --> 02:56.350
- Hurts like hell,
but I've dealt with worse.

02:57.525 --> 03:00.310
[sighs]
I'd kill for a soft mattress.

03:00.354 --> 03:02.921
- Or a hot shower.

03:04.271 --> 03:05.489
- We're gonna get out of here.

03:05.533 --> 03:07.448
Just need to hang
in a little longer.

03:07.491 --> 03:10.190
- Yeah, I'm just really
missing my daughter right now.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.368
- I get it.

03:14.411 --> 03:16.631
I've got a son up there.

03:16.674 --> 03:17.675
Here.
[both chuckle]

03:17.719 --> 03:20.461
That's Andrew, my wife, Julia.

03:20.504 --> 03:22.724
I know she's taking
good care of him.

03:22.767 --> 03:26.031
She's always been
the levelheaded one.

03:26.075 --> 03:29.296
Married 25 years this November.

03:30.949 --> 03:32.516
[click]

03:32.560 --> 03:34.779
Got to hold on
to the last bit of battery.

03:37.304 --> 03:39.958
You married, Eve?

03:40.002 --> 03:41.786
- Separated.

03:44.311 --> 03:46.530
Last couple years
were pretty hard.

03:47.923 --> 03:50.186
- Maybe coming down here,

03:50.230 --> 03:52.623
going through something
like this,

03:52.667 --> 03:54.495
may change things
when you get back.

03:57.585 --> 04:00.675
[explosive rumbling]

04:03.852 --> 04:06.898
[dramatic music]

04:06.942 --> 04:13.905
♪

04:19.607 --> 04:21.261
What the hell is that?

04:23.785 --> 04:25.874
[whooshing]

04:34.404 --> 04:37.494
[intense dramatic music]

04:38.626 --> 04:42.282
[indistinct chatter]

04:44.632 --> 04:46.024
- If you're going
after that plane,

04:46.068 --> 04:48.549
I'm coming with you--
and don't tell me I can't.

04:48.592 --> 04:51.378
I'm sore, but I feel fine.

04:51.421 --> 04:53.467
I'm not letting you go alone.

04:55.904 --> 04:58.254
- All right, check with Sam.
If he says you're good,

04:58.298 --> 05:00.082
you can come.

05:02.171 --> 05:03.955
- Infection's almost gone.

05:03.999 --> 05:06.262
You're a fast healer, kid,
I'll give you that.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.351
He can go.
Just keep taking

05:08.395 --> 05:10.266
the antibiotics
and don't try to push it.

05:10.310 --> 05:12.181
- So what's your plan, Eve?
- Well, the smoke's

05:12.224 --> 05:14.139
in that direction,
so that's where I'm headed.

05:14.183 --> 05:15.489
- Yeah, so am I.

05:15.532 --> 05:16.968
That plane came through
the same light we did.

05:17.012 --> 05:18.883
Whoever was flying might
be able to get us out of here.

05:18.927 --> 05:21.146
- Or they're dead.
Not to mention

05:21.190 --> 05:22.583
they went down miles from here.

05:22.626 --> 05:24.628
Lots of saber-tooths
between here and there.

05:24.672 --> 05:26.064
Sure you want to risk it?

05:26.108 --> 05:27.979
- What other choice do we have?
- Sam's right.

05:28.023 --> 05:29.546
We've been lucky enough
to survive till now.

05:29.590 --> 05:31.374
How long do you think
that's gonna last?

05:31.418 --> 05:32.462
- I'll be right back.

05:32.506 --> 05:33.768
Got to grab something
from my car.

05:33.811 --> 05:35.639
- Now listen up,
only a small group should go.

05:35.683 --> 05:38.816
No more than five--less scent
for the animals to track.

05:38.860 --> 05:41.123
- Scott,
you're the expert down here.

05:41.166 --> 05:43.038
You should come.
- Sure.

05:43.081 --> 05:44.735
Plane falls out of the sky,
I'm your man.

05:44.779 --> 05:46.911
- Riley, you should go too.

05:47.521 --> 05:48.826
- Excuse me?

05:48.870 --> 05:50.393
- Well,
I can't make it that far,

05:50.437 --> 05:52.177
and you have medical training.

05:52.221 --> 05:53.744
That pilot could be hurt.

05:53.788 --> 05:57.357
Just keep your eyes open
out there and listen to Eve.

05:58.967 --> 06:01.665
- Better get going--that smoke
trail's starting to fade.

06:01.709 --> 06:03.841
- Okay.
I'll go grab Lucas.

06:04.755 --> 06:07.845
[suspenseful music]

06:09.238 --> 06:10.413
[metallic click]

06:10.457 --> 06:16.506
♪

06:19.466 --> 06:21.859
- What?
- We're ready to go.

06:23.034 --> 06:25.123
- Then what are we
standing here for?

06:30.259 --> 06:33.393
[exotic bird calls]

06:34.045 --> 06:36.657
- Smoke trail's gone.
- It's okay.

06:36.700 --> 06:38.963
We just need to keep going
in that direction.

06:39.007 --> 06:41.444
- Hey, Lucas.

06:41.488 --> 06:42.750
I never got a chance
to say thanks

06:42.793 --> 06:45.492
for getting my dad back
to the clearing.

06:45.535 --> 06:47.450
He probably would be dead
if it weren't for you.

06:47.494 --> 06:49.321
- Way I hear it, you saved him.

06:49.365 --> 06:52.368
People said you did some
surgery to repair his back.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.501
That's not bad.

06:54.544 --> 06:57.852
- You know, I do what I can.
[both laugh]

06:58.722 --> 07:01.159
Pick up the pace, Scott.
You're dragging ass.

07:01.203 --> 07:02.552
- Fine back here, thanks.

07:04.424 --> 07:05.555
- Look.

07:05.599 --> 07:08.515
[tense music]

07:08.558 --> 07:10.299
♪

07:10.342 --> 07:12.170
- Where's the pilot?

07:12.214 --> 07:13.433
[tiger growls]

07:13.476 --> 07:15.478
[gunshots fire]

07:15.522 --> 07:16.610
- Where's that coming from?

07:18.481 --> 07:21.441
[leaves and branches crunch]

07:27.621 --> 07:30.537
[dramatic musical swell]

07:30.580 --> 07:32.277
♪

07:32.321 --> 07:33.453
- Levi?

07:38.370 --> 07:38.545
.

07:38.588 --> 07:41.678
- Eve.
- Oh, my--

07:41.722 --> 07:43.854
[soft dramatic music]

07:43.898 --> 07:45.552
- Uncle Levi.

07:47.336 --> 07:49.773
Are you okay?
- Yeah.

07:49.817 --> 07:51.209
I can't believe
I'm saying this,

07:51.253 --> 07:53.255
but I think I just shot
at a saber-tooth.

07:53.298 --> 07:55.257
- Hold on, how do you guys
know each other?

07:55.300 --> 07:57.781
- Levi flew in the Air Force
with my dad.

07:57.825 --> 07:59.914
- So this is a rescue mission?

07:59.957 --> 08:02.351
- I was sent here
to bring you all home.

08:02.394 --> 08:04.701
Only now I'm not sure
if I can.

08:04.745 --> 08:07.748
[tense music]

08:07.791 --> 08:10.925
- Are they sending anyone else?
- No, just me.

08:10.968 --> 08:13.971
That's why I gotta find my
plane, see if it can still fly.

08:14.015 --> 08:16.234
- You think it's possible?
- I don't know.

08:16.278 --> 08:17.801
One of the engines went out
right before

08:17.845 --> 08:20.108
I went through the light,
but doesn't mean it won't work.

08:20.151 --> 08:22.240
- And when you say light,
you mean that portal, right?

08:22.284 --> 08:23.807
I just want to confirm
that with you,

08:23.851 --> 08:25.592
because that still
blows my mind.

08:25.635 --> 08:27.942
- People who sent me,
they can't explain it either.

08:27.985 --> 08:29.160
- What about the rest
of the world?

08:29.204 --> 08:30.422
Do they know what happened
to us?

08:30.466 --> 08:32.512
- No.
They're keeping things quiet

08:32.555 --> 08:33.948
until we can
get you guys back home.

08:33.991 --> 08:35.602
- Classic government cover-up.

08:35.645 --> 08:37.908
- Levi,

08:37.952 --> 08:39.431
do you know if Izzy's okay?

08:39.475 --> 08:40.998
- Yeah, yeah.
She's fine.

08:41.042 --> 08:42.347
- [sighs]

08:42.391 --> 08:44.654
- A--And what
about our families?

08:44.698 --> 08:46.177
Do they just think we're dead?

08:50.051 --> 08:51.574
- Look, I'm sorry.

08:51.618 --> 08:53.141
I know you guys have
a lot of questions,

08:53.184 --> 08:55.360
but right now,
we need to find my plane.

08:55.404 --> 08:57.580
When I ejected, I was heading
towards an open field.

08:57.624 --> 08:59.669
Problem is I haven't been able
to get a signal

08:59.713 --> 09:01.279
on the homing beacon,

09:01.323 --> 09:02.629
and then I got turned around
in the forest.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.239
- That's all right.
We, uh--we saw it go down,

09:04.282 --> 09:05.414
and we were heading
that direction anyway.

09:05.457 --> 09:07.590
- If it's still in one piece,

09:07.634 --> 09:10.506
I may be able to fix it,
fly us all home.

09:14.815 --> 09:16.817
- Government officials
have yet to comment

09:16.860 --> 09:18.340
on reports of an explosion

09:18.383 --> 09:20.951
from inside the sinkhole
late last night.

09:20.995 --> 09:23.606
The blast reverberated
through the La Brea area,

09:23.650 --> 09:25.303
rattling a community
still reeling

09:25.347 --> 09:26.870
from this week's
devastating events.

09:26.914 --> 09:29.786
The cause of the explosion
remains unclear...

09:29.830 --> 09:32.746
[rumbling, clattering]

09:37.141 --> 09:38.752
- Dad!
- Iz!

09:39.840 --> 09:41.145
Iz?

09:41.189 --> 09:43.147
Okay, okay.

09:43.191 --> 09:44.366
I got you, I got you.

09:44.409 --> 09:47.499
[house rattles and creaks]

09:50.024 --> 09:52.722
Hey.
It's over.

09:52.766 --> 09:54.681
It's over.
Okay?

09:56.291 --> 09:58.902
- Are you guys okay?
- Yeah, we're good.

09:58.946 --> 10:01.513
[phone buzzes, bleeps]

10:01.557 --> 10:03.646
What is it?
- It's the earthquake alert.

10:03.690 --> 10:06.693
It says the epicenter
is right near the sinkhole.

10:06.736 --> 10:11.001
[suspenseful music]

10:11.045 --> 10:12.002
- You don't think
that has something to do

10:12.046 --> 10:13.351
with Uncle Levi's plane?

10:13.395 --> 10:15.832
- I don't know.
I gotta go talk to Dr. Nathan,

10:15.876 --> 10:16.964
find out what's going on.

10:17.007 --> 10:23.405
♪

10:23.448 --> 10:26.538
[high-pitched ringing]

10:31.718 --> 10:32.719
- Levi.

10:34.895 --> 10:37.637
- [breathes shakily]

10:40.335 --> 10:42.206
[knocks]
Dr. Nathan?

10:42.250 --> 10:45.166
[suspenseful music]

10:45.209 --> 10:52.347
♪

10:55.089 --> 10:58.048
[dramatic music]

10:58.092 --> 11:05.229
♪

11:08.015 --> 11:11.322
- Gavin.
What are you doing here?

11:11.366 --> 11:13.281
- I just need to talk
to Dr. Nathan.

11:13.324 --> 11:15.718
- She's, uh, she's taking
the day for herself.

11:15.762 --> 11:17.981
After what happened to Levi,
you can imagine there was a lot

11:18.025 --> 11:20.462
of blame going around,
and she took the brunt of it.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.551
- Markman, Levi is alive.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.728
- You saw him?

11:25.772 --> 11:28.296
- Somehow he survived.

11:28.339 --> 11:31.255
He's down there with my family.

11:31.299 --> 11:33.518
- Well, I'm, uh,
I'm glad to hear that.

11:33.562 --> 11:37.784
But, uh, unfortunately,
that doesn't change anything.

11:37.827 --> 11:38.828
- How can you say that?

11:38.872 --> 11:40.874
[stammering]
He made it through.

11:40.917 --> 11:43.398
All we have to do is figure out
what went wrong with his plane.

11:43.441 --> 11:46.488
- Gavin, there's not gonna
be another rescue mission.

11:46.531 --> 11:49.491
About an hour
after Levi's plane exploded,

11:49.534 --> 11:52.233
our geologists noticed seismic
activity in the sinkhole.

11:52.276 --> 11:55.062
Now, that's what caused
the earthquake you felt.

11:55.105 --> 11:56.498
We can't risk sending
in another plane

11:56.541 --> 11:57.934
and causing an even bigger one.

11:57.978 --> 11:59.414
There's too many lives at risk.

11:59.457 --> 12:01.329
- My wife
and son are down there.

12:02.809 --> 12:06.508
- I'm sorry.
I mean, I really am.

12:08.771 --> 12:10.251
Listen to me, Gavin,

12:10.294 --> 12:13.341
there's nothing else
that we can do right now.

12:17.084 --> 12:20.957
- I understand.
- Come on, I'll walk you out.

12:21.001 --> 12:24.091
[uneasy music]

12:24.134 --> 12:27.964
♪

12:28.008 --> 12:30.880
[animals chattering]

12:34.841 --> 12:37.321
- [breathes heavily]

12:37.365 --> 12:39.715
- You good?
- Yeah.

12:41.151 --> 12:42.892
- Oh, no,
you are definitely not okay.

12:42.936 --> 12:45.155
What's going on?

12:45.199 --> 12:47.331
- I, uh,
cut myself when I ejected.

12:47.375 --> 12:49.812
But it's fine.
- Okay, you're losing blood.

12:49.856 --> 12:52.162
- Damn.
- Just a scratch, bud.

12:52.206 --> 12:55.252
- Josh, why don't you go to the
brook and get him some water?

12:59.430 --> 13:01.737
- Hey.
Wait up.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.347
I need to tell you something.

13:03.391 --> 13:05.132
Remember when I told you
that the heroin I buried

13:05.175 --> 13:07.177
probably belonged
to someone who died?

13:07.221 --> 13:08.788
- Yeah.
- I was wrong.

13:08.831 --> 13:10.485
It's Lucas's.

13:10.528 --> 13:14.097
And he's got that gun.
- Jesus.

13:14.750 --> 13:15.925
You said you buried it, right?
- Yeah.

13:15.969 --> 13:17.535
- Just unbury it.

13:17.579 --> 13:20.321
- I was stoned when I did it.
And it was dark.

13:20.364 --> 13:21.496
I don't think
I remember where it is.

13:21.539 --> 13:23.846
- You're serious?
What's wrong with you?

13:23.890 --> 13:25.935
- A lot.
I'm sorry.

13:27.632 --> 13:30.157
- Look, as long as we don't
say anything to him about it,

13:30.200 --> 13:31.201
he'll never find out.

13:31.245 --> 13:32.594
- Okay.
- All right?

13:33.464 --> 13:34.944
We'll be fine.

13:39.949 --> 13:41.385
- That should stop the bleeding
for now.

13:41.429 --> 13:42.822
- Thanks, Riley.
- Yeah.

13:42.865 --> 13:45.389
- Here you go.
- Thanks, bud.

13:46.173 --> 13:47.696
- You okay?

13:49.437 --> 13:50.830
- Yeah, I'm good.

13:50.873 --> 13:53.223
[device beeps]

13:53.267 --> 13:56.400
[suspenseful music]

13:56.444 --> 13:57.880
It's picking up the plane.

13:57.924 --> 14:01.536
- How far?
- Less than a mile from here.

14:01.579 --> 14:05.105
♪

14:05.148 --> 14:08.064
- All right.
See if it starts.

14:08.108 --> 14:09.326
[engine grinding]

14:09.370 --> 14:11.024
- How many times do I have
to tell you,

14:11.067 --> 14:12.460
this is a waste of time.

14:12.503 --> 14:14.505
- You got something better
to do?

14:14.549 --> 14:16.159
- Sounds like you almost
got it started.

14:16.203 --> 14:18.509
Working car could be useful.

14:18.553 --> 14:20.424
I'd keep at it, Tony.
- Thanks, Sam.

14:20.468 --> 14:23.427
- Anyone hungry?
- Nice work, guys.

14:23.471 --> 14:25.212
- Well,
Eddie here gets the credit.

14:25.255 --> 14:28.868
- Who knew those Boy Scout
skills would come in handy?

14:28.911 --> 14:31.305
Ty, you said I catch them,
you clean them.

14:31.348 --> 14:33.698
- Ugh.
- Take it from here.

14:33.742 --> 14:34.830
- Yeah.

14:36.832 --> 14:38.965
- You have no idea
how to clean them, do you?

14:39.008 --> 14:42.490
- Not in the slightest.
- [chuckles]

14:47.582 --> 14:50.933
[ominous music]

14:50.977 --> 14:52.456
[leaves shuffle]

15:03.337 --> 15:06.427
- Lilly.
Why aren't you reading?

15:07.471 --> 15:10.170
- I am.

15:10.213 --> 15:13.738
[people talking indistinctly]

15:13.782 --> 15:15.392
- I see.

15:16.611 --> 15:18.961
- I just like them.
They were nice to me.

15:19.005 --> 15:21.224
- You don't know anything
about them.

15:21.268 --> 15:23.531
- Maybe I can get to know them.

15:23.574 --> 15:25.228
- Absolutely not.

15:25.272 --> 15:27.839
- I don't see how it'd hurt
if I talk to them.

15:27.883 --> 15:29.493
I promise I'll never
say anything about us.

15:29.537 --> 15:30.799
- Lilly, you know the rules.

15:30.842 --> 15:32.496
You're not allowed to talk
to anyone.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.977
- Those were his rules.
And he's dead.

15:36.892 --> 15:40.156
- Our father loved us,
And you will respect him.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.375
And me.

15:44.247 --> 15:46.989
Lilly.
Get back here!

15:47.033 --> 15:50.297
- [sobs]

15:50.340 --> 15:53.300
[ominous music]

15:53.343 --> 15:57.043
♪

15:57.086 --> 16:00.002
[leaves shuffling]

16:00.046 --> 16:03.179
[intense music]

16:03.223 --> 16:04.964
[cries out]

16:05.007 --> 16:11.448
♪

16:11.492 --> 16:12.884
[panting]

16:18.412 --> 16:20.066
[screams]

16:24.200 --> 16:24.418
.

16:24.461 --> 16:25.810
- Lilly!

16:25.854 --> 16:28.900
[suspenseful music]

16:30.076 --> 16:32.339
Lilly!
Lilly!

16:35.516 --> 16:37.083
Oh, my God!

16:37.126 --> 16:38.780
[indistinct chatter]

16:38.823 --> 16:44.046
♪

16:44.090 --> 16:47.528
- Eddie!
- Jeez...

16:47.571 --> 16:49.530
what happened to him?

16:49.573 --> 16:51.314
- Veronica,
did you see anything?

16:51.358 --> 16:53.403
- No, I--
I heard Lilly scream and when--

16:53.447 --> 16:56.319
when I got here,
he was already like that.

16:56.363 --> 17:00.454
- Lilly,
do you know what happened?

17:02.804 --> 17:04.719
Lilly?

17:04.762 --> 17:06.373
- She's in shock.

17:06.416 --> 17:10.159
- You should take her back.
- Come on, Lilly.

17:11.334 --> 17:13.206
- This is great.
As if things weren't

17:13.249 --> 17:14.859
bad enough,
now we gotta worry about this.

17:14.903 --> 17:16.035
- What could have
done this to him?

17:16.078 --> 17:17.427
- What if this happens
to one of us?

17:17.471 --> 17:18.863
How are we gonna
defend ourselves?

17:18.907 --> 17:20.039
We're sitting ducks here, man.

17:20.082 --> 17:21.301
- Hey, hey, just relax.

17:21.344 --> 17:23.477
We're not gonna solve anything
by panicking.

17:23.520 --> 17:26.523
- I agree, and we need to treat
this place like a crime scene,

17:26.567 --> 17:28.090
see if there's any evidence
that can tell us

17:28.134 --> 17:29.222
who or what did this.

17:29.265 --> 17:31.050
- I'll take a look at the body,

17:31.093 --> 17:32.616
try to determine
cause of death.

17:32.660 --> 17:35.445
- What about the rest of us?
What are we gonna do?

17:35.489 --> 17:38.274
- Go back to the clearing
and stick together.

17:38.318 --> 17:39.928
Nobody goes anywhere alone

17:39.971 --> 17:41.712
until we figure out
what's going on.

17:41.756 --> 17:44.237
Go!
- Okay.

17:44.280 --> 17:45.281
- [sighs]

17:47.066 --> 17:50.069
[intense music]

17:50.112 --> 17:53.159
[birds call, insects chirp]

17:58.729 --> 18:00.122
- Plane's on the other side.

18:00.166 --> 18:01.428
- Looks pretty deep.

18:05.258 --> 18:07.782
- I can touch the bottom.
It's only a few feet.

18:07.825 --> 18:11.090
We can walk it.
- Oh, good.

18:12.395 --> 18:15.398
- Relax, man.
Little water never hurt anyone.

18:15.442 --> 18:17.313
- Actually,
that's where you're wrong.

18:17.357 --> 18:19.663
I kind of have a major fear
of water.

18:19.707 --> 18:21.839
Even a bath can
be a traumatic experience.

18:21.883 --> 18:24.451
- Why does that
not surprise me?

18:24.494 --> 18:26.148
- I'm really not sure
I can do this, Riley.

18:26.192 --> 18:29.064
- Do you want to get
to the plane or not?

18:29.108 --> 18:32.111
- I got you, man.
I won't let you drown.

18:32.154 --> 18:35.070
- That's why you have
a planet named after you.

18:35.114 --> 18:38.073
[ominous music]

18:38.117 --> 18:45.211
♪

18:50.477 --> 18:53.654
- Dr. Nathan, it's Gavin again.

18:53.697 --> 18:56.657
When you get this,
please call me back.

19:00.791 --> 19:03.751
[mysterious music]

19:03.794 --> 19:05.535
[footsteps approaching]

19:05.579 --> 19:08.712
- Dad, what did Dr. Nathan say
about the earthquake?

19:08.756 --> 19:10.497
- I didn't talk to her.

19:10.540 --> 19:13.978
But Agent Markman told me it
was triggered by Levi's crash.

19:14.022 --> 19:16.633
- So what does that mean?

19:16.677 --> 19:19.158
- They're shutting down
the rescue mission.

19:20.898 --> 19:23.466
- What?
No, they can't.

19:23.510 --> 19:24.728
Mom and Josh are alive
down there.

19:24.772 --> 19:27.731
- I know.
Levi is too.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.996
- He survived?

19:32.040 --> 19:34.216
- Yeah.
I saw him.

19:34.260 --> 19:36.523
He's with Eve and Josh.

19:36.566 --> 19:38.307
We're going to find another way
to save them, Iz.

19:38.351 --> 19:40.918
Okay?
I think the answer

19:40.962 --> 19:42.659
might be in this file.

19:42.703 --> 19:45.053
So Dr. Nathan only mentioned
the Mojave sinkhole,

19:45.096 --> 19:48.404
but this, it says fourth event,

19:48.448 --> 19:51.320
which means
there are more out there.

19:51.364 --> 19:53.322
- You think one of them
could lead to Mom and Josh?

19:53.366 --> 19:54.976
- It's possible.
That's why I need to talk

19:55.019 --> 19:57.326
to Dr. Nathan because
she could help us find one.

19:57.370 --> 19:59.676
Problem is I can't
get ahold of her.

19:59.720 --> 20:02.026
- Well, what about her?
Maybe she can help.

20:02.070 --> 20:03.941
Says her name's
Rebecca Aldridge.

20:03.985 --> 20:05.769
- Look her up, Iz.
I don't know anything about her

20:05.813 --> 20:08.337
but she's clearly involved
in all this.

20:10.687 --> 20:12.036
- Found her.

20:12.080 --> 20:14.256
Says she owns a horse ranch
in San Luis Obispo.

20:14.300 --> 20:16.737
- What would a rancher
have to do with all this?

20:16.780 --> 20:19.218
- I don't know.
Let's go find out.

20:19.261 --> 20:21.655
- Good idea.

20:21.698 --> 20:25.224
[ominous music]

20:25.267 --> 20:28.096
- You okay?
- Not at all.

20:32.405 --> 20:35.016
- Give me your hand.

20:35.059 --> 20:37.148
Come on,
I'm not gonna hurt you.

20:37.192 --> 20:39.238
- Yeah, why would you?

20:44.982 --> 20:46.941
- What the hell?
- What's wrong?

20:46.984 --> 20:48.421
- Something just
touched my leg.

20:49.552 --> 20:51.859
There's something in the water.

20:55.819 --> 20:57.299
- Riley!

20:58.909 --> 21:00.084
- Riley!

21:00.128 --> 21:02.913
[eerie music]

21:02.957 --> 21:08.310
♪

21:08.354 --> 21:09.790
- I don't know
where she went.

21:14.751 --> 21:15.926
- She's over there!

21:15.970 --> 21:17.711
- [muffled screams]

21:22.890 --> 21:24.152
[muffled gunshots]

21:29.113 --> 21:31.115
- [gasping for air]

21:31.159 --> 21:34.336
[all panting]

21:35.511 --> 21:37.644
- You okay?
- Yeah.

21:37.687 --> 21:39.298
- Go, go, go.

21:46.957 --> 21:47.175
.

21:47.218 --> 21:49.090
- Thanks for helping me
look around.

21:49.133 --> 21:50.047
- I'm gonna guess you never saw

21:50.091 --> 21:51.919
anything like this
back at home.

21:51.962 --> 21:54.661
- That's the understatement
of the year.

21:54.704 --> 21:56.837
- How long you been
in law enforcement?

21:56.880 --> 21:58.882
- Feels like my whole life.

21:58.926 --> 22:01.015
My dad was the sheriff
of my hometown.

22:01.058 --> 22:03.365
I joined the force
20 years ago.

22:03.409 --> 22:05.280
It's all I've ever known.

22:06.629 --> 22:10.241
- I'm not finding anything.
- Yeah, me neither.

22:10.285 --> 22:11.982
It's strange.
Whatever killed him

22:12.026 --> 22:14.724
didn't leave a trace
of itself behind.

22:14.768 --> 22:16.291
- Hey, guys!

22:18.859 --> 22:20.600
- What do you got?

22:20.643 --> 22:23.385
- Well, obviously, I couldn't
perform a full autopsy,

22:23.429 --> 22:25.561
but I'm pretty certain
he was electrocuted.

22:25.605 --> 22:27.650
- Electrocuted?

22:27.694 --> 22:30.914
How is that possible?
We're in 10,000 BC.

22:30.958 --> 22:34.831
- I don't know, but these
burn patterns can happen

22:34.875 --> 22:36.616
when someone is struck
by lightning.

22:36.659 --> 22:38.444
They're called
Lichtenberg figures.

22:38.487 --> 22:40.228
- Considering there hasn't
been any lightning

22:40.271 --> 22:42.622
since we got here,
something else caused this.

22:42.665 --> 22:45.146
And there's only one person
who knows the answer to that.

22:46.321 --> 22:47.757
- Lilly.

22:47.801 --> 22:48.932
- Kids don't
make great witnesses

22:48.976 --> 22:50.325
under normal circumstances.

22:50.369 --> 22:52.675
Add in the fact
she doesn't talk--

22:54.590 --> 22:56.940
Word is you're a psychiatrist.

22:58.246 --> 22:59.378
- I am.
- Do you think you could

22:59.421 --> 23:00.422
break through to her,

23:00.466 --> 23:02.468
get her to open up?

23:02.511 --> 23:04.774
- I can try.
- Good.

23:04.818 --> 23:07.777
'Cause we need to find out
what she knows.

23:13.479 --> 23:15.959
- That was so close back there.
For a second, I thought--

23:16.003 --> 23:19.180
- Don't worry.
I'm good.

23:22.270 --> 23:23.880
- How you doing?

23:23.924 --> 23:25.708
- [sighs]
Oh, you know,

23:25.752 --> 23:30.713
scarred for life,
but beyond that, fine.

23:30.757 --> 23:33.324
- Uh, I'm fine too
if anyone was asking.

23:33.977 --> 23:36.197
[dramatic music]

23:36.240 --> 23:37.328
- There it is.

23:37.372 --> 23:42.899
♪

23:42.943 --> 23:45.641
- There's fire damage
to the right engine.

23:45.685 --> 23:48.252
The left one looks okay.
- Oh, thank God.

23:48.296 --> 23:50.341
- Dude, you crashed
in the middle of a field.

23:50.385 --> 23:52.343
Even if you can fly, there's
no room for you to take off.

23:52.387 --> 23:54.389
- It's designed
for vertical takeoff.

23:54.433 --> 23:55.782
We don't need a runway.

23:55.825 --> 23:58.001
Come on,
I'm gonna do a systems check,

23:58.045 --> 24:00.526
see the extent of the damage.

24:00.569 --> 24:05.226
[exciting music]

24:05.269 --> 24:07.010
Okay.

24:07.054 --> 24:10.144
[machinery beeping
and whirring]

24:11.101 --> 24:13.321
Computer and electrical
systems are functioning.

24:13.364 --> 24:15.366
It's a good sign.

24:16.498 --> 24:19.283
Come on, come on.
Work.

24:19.327 --> 24:21.372
[error message beeping]
Damn it.

24:21.416 --> 24:22.722
- What's wrong?

24:22.765 --> 24:23.940
- The right
engine compressor's dead.

24:23.984 --> 24:25.551
- But you have a spare, right?

24:25.594 --> 24:26.856
- It's not a tire.

24:26.900 --> 24:28.771
Compressors
are sophisticated machines.

24:28.815 --> 24:30.033
- When did you
become an expert?

24:30.077 --> 24:32.079
- My dad's a pilot.
We used to work

24:32.122 --> 24:33.602
on old planes together.

24:33.646 --> 24:36.649
- Okay, can we fix it?

24:36.692 --> 24:38.346
- Not without the parts I need.

24:38.389 --> 24:41.741
- They won't be invented
for another 12,000 years.

24:54.884 --> 24:56.103
- Couple hours in the car
and you've already

24:56.146 --> 24:58.497
given up on conversation.

24:58.540 --> 25:01.761
- It's a five-hour drive.
I'm pacing myself.

25:03.327 --> 25:06.156
- Remember that road trip
we took to the Grand Canyon?

25:07.723 --> 25:09.551
- Yeah.
- Your mom made us leave

25:09.595 --> 25:11.118
in the middle of the night

25:11.161 --> 25:14.077
so we could get there
before sunrise.

25:14.121 --> 25:15.514
[laughs]
She packed a whole bunch

25:15.557 --> 25:18.125
of food so we wouldn't
have to waste time stopping.

25:18.168 --> 25:20.170
- Oh, right, the tuna.

25:20.214 --> 25:22.433
- Tuna.
- Totally forgot.

25:22.477 --> 25:25.959
- Why she thought that was
a good idea, I'll never know.

25:26.002 --> 25:28.744
- By the time we got there,
we missed the sunrise.

25:28.788 --> 25:33.053
Not a great first day.
- It was.

25:34.184 --> 25:36.491
Because we were all together.

25:42.671 --> 25:44.586
That was our last
family vacation.

25:44.630 --> 25:47.720
[tender music]

25:47.763 --> 25:54.901
♪

25:57.773 --> 25:58.992
- Figured you guys
would be hungry.

25:59.035 --> 26:00.646
I've got plenty of MREs.

26:00.689 --> 26:02.125
- Thank God.
No more mushrooms.

26:02.169 --> 26:03.562
- Let's bring these back
to the clearing.

26:03.605 --> 26:04.954
There's gonna be a lot
of hungry people over there.

26:04.998 --> 26:06.782
- Hold on, aren't you gonna
radio back home,

26:06.826 --> 26:08.044
tell them to send more help?

26:08.088 --> 26:10.133
- I tried the radio,
didn't work.

26:10.177 --> 26:12.092
- Seriously?
- There was no guarantee

26:12.135 --> 26:14.050
I'd be able to communicate
once I got down here.

26:14.094 --> 26:15.748
- You knew that
and you still took the mission?

26:15.791 --> 26:17.488
Why the hell would you do that?

26:20.274 --> 26:22.319
- It's gonna be dark soon.
We should head back.

26:22.363 --> 26:25.192
We can regroup and come up with
a new plan when we get there.

26:25.235 --> 26:26.933
- I gotta grab one more thing.

26:26.976 --> 26:29.762
[dramatic music]

26:29.805 --> 26:36.899
♪

26:49.520 --> 26:52.436
[device beeping]

26:59.618 --> 27:00.662
This doesn't make sense.

27:00.706 --> 27:03.099
- Hey, we gotta get going.

27:03.143 --> 27:04.884
What's up?
- Plane's radar system,

27:04.927 --> 27:06.886
it's picking up a signal.
- From where?

27:06.929 --> 27:09.497
- About 5 miles south of here.

27:10.933 --> 27:13.240
- What could be
sending a signal?

27:13.283 --> 27:15.024
- Maybe someone's out there,

27:15.068 --> 27:17.331
someone who could
help get us home.

27:18.637 --> 27:20.943
- Okay, so we camp
here tonight, and then we--

27:20.987 --> 27:22.641
we go first thing
in the morning.

27:29.822 --> 27:29.996
.

27:30.039 --> 27:33.042
[insects chirping]

27:33.086 --> 27:36.002
[distant bellowing]

27:39.788 --> 27:41.355
- Okay, I don't know
what's more frightening,

27:41.398 --> 27:43.270
that wild animal
or the fact that your radar

27:43.313 --> 27:45.359
is picking up something
out there.

27:45.402 --> 27:47.970
- What are you saying, man?

27:48.014 --> 27:49.885
You'd rather just go back
and not find out what it is?

27:49.929 --> 27:52.758
- Oh, no,
I'm just making conversation.

27:52.801 --> 27:54.673
The food tastes delicious,
Captain.

27:54.716 --> 27:57.632
- I don't think anybody's
ever said that about MREs.

27:59.329 --> 28:01.810
- Is your arm okay?
- It's better,

28:01.854 --> 28:03.420
thanks to Riley.

28:03.464 --> 28:06.989
- Yeah, I had some on-the-job
training the last few days.

28:07.033 --> 28:09.252
I did an emergency
spinal procedure on my dad.

28:09.296 --> 28:10.950
No big deal.

28:10.993 --> 28:13.082
- How'd you pull that off?
- No!

28:13.126 --> 28:14.997
You know what, you don't
have to talk about that.

28:15.041 --> 28:16.695
Who cares, really?
- Uh, no, I--

28:16.738 --> 28:18.522
I find it pretty impressive.

28:18.566 --> 28:20.176
- Thanks, Eve.

28:20.220 --> 28:21.830
Besides, I couldn't have
done it without you guys.

28:21.874 --> 28:24.311
- We should talk
about something else.

28:24.354 --> 28:25.660
- Why?
Scott deserves the credit.

28:25.704 --> 28:28.968
I would have never thought
to use the heroin.

28:29.011 --> 28:31.797
[tense music]

28:31.840 --> 28:33.799
- Sorry, what'd you say?
- Yeah.

28:33.842 --> 28:35.757
We used it as an anesthetic.
It was genius.

28:35.801 --> 28:38.151
- People throw around that word
too loosely these days.

28:38.194 --> 28:40.283
- Wait,
somebody has heroin down here?

28:40.327 --> 28:41.981
That's a little concerning.

28:42.024 --> 28:43.286
- Yeah,
Scott thought the same thing,

28:43.330 --> 28:46.855
which is why he got rid of it,
so we're good.

28:49.640 --> 28:53.775
- Well,
I'm just glad everyone's safe.

28:53.819 --> 28:56.735
Would be terrible
if someone got hurt.

28:58.475 --> 29:00.564
- Well, I'm gonna
go get some more food.

29:00.608 --> 29:03.524
You're right, Scott,
this isn't so bad.

29:03.567 --> 29:09.095
♪

29:09.138 --> 29:11.140
[ominous music]

29:11.184 --> 29:13.882
- We still don't know who
or what killed Eddie.

29:13.926 --> 29:16.972
But right now,
we need to stick together.

29:17.016 --> 29:20.759
Everyone sleeps by the fire.
There's safety in numbers.

29:20.802 --> 29:23.109
- Unless someone here did it.

29:25.198 --> 29:26.765
I mean, I know I didn't do it,

29:26.808 --> 29:29.768
but who's to say
one of you didn't?

29:29.811 --> 29:31.900
- You want to sleep
by yourself?

29:31.944 --> 29:33.336
Have at it.

29:33.380 --> 29:35.425
- We need
to stand watch tonight.

29:35.469 --> 29:36.992
I'll take the first shift.

29:37.036 --> 29:38.777
- What about the group that
went looking for the plane?

29:38.820 --> 29:41.780
They could be in danger too.

29:42.781 --> 29:46.045
- I know, but there's nothing
we can do right now.

29:46.088 --> 29:47.698
Everyone get some sleep.

29:47.742 --> 29:50.614
[people chatting indistinctly]

29:50.658 --> 29:52.051
They'll be okay.

29:52.094 --> 29:53.487
- This isn't the first
sleepless night

29:53.530 --> 29:55.445
I'll have because of Lucas.

29:55.489 --> 29:57.056
- Believe me, I get it.

29:57.099 --> 30:01.625
- I wish it would get easier,
but it never does.

30:03.149 --> 30:05.586
- Why don't you try
to get some sleep?

30:05.629 --> 30:07.936
- Thanks.

30:20.949 --> 30:22.342
- You two should
join the others.

30:22.385 --> 30:24.474
It's safer.
- We're fine here.

30:24.518 --> 30:26.650
I'll keep the doors locked.

30:26.694 --> 30:28.391
- I'd like to speak with Lilly
in the morning,

30:28.435 --> 30:29.523
find out what she saw.

30:29.566 --> 30:30.959
I realize she doesn't speak,

30:31.003 --> 30:34.745
but there are other ways
to communicate.

30:37.574 --> 30:40.534
- I'm sorry, I don't want her
to have to relive that.

30:40.577 --> 30:42.753
- I understand.
You want to protect her,

30:42.797 --> 30:44.886
but I've worked with children
who have suffered trauma.

30:44.930 --> 30:46.018
If it becomes too much,
I won't push.

30:46.061 --> 30:48.237
- The answer's no.
- Veronica,

30:48.281 --> 30:50.500
I can't take no for an answer.

30:50.544 --> 30:52.241
The safety of everyone here

30:52.285 --> 30:54.200
depends on finding out
what Lilly knows.

30:56.332 --> 30:59.596
Get some sleep.
I'll see you in the morning.

30:59.640 --> 31:01.250
Don't forget
to lock those doors.

31:06.734 --> 31:09.650
[uneasy music]

31:09.693 --> 31:13.610
♪

31:13.654 --> 31:16.875
- Hey.
Is he still staring?

31:20.966 --> 31:22.010
- Yep.

31:23.577 --> 31:25.840
- He's gonna kill me, isn't he?

31:25.884 --> 31:27.886
- I really couldn't say.

31:32.978 --> 31:36.111
- They can tell you all they
want about going to 10,000 BC,

31:36.155 --> 31:39.158
but once you're here,
it's a totally different story.

31:39.201 --> 31:40.899
- Tell me about it.

31:47.862 --> 31:50.256
- You know, I'm not sure
what I was more nervous about,

31:50.299 --> 31:52.258
flying into a sinkhole
or seeing you.

31:55.043 --> 31:57.741
- Is that why you never called?

31:57.785 --> 31:59.091
- I wanted to reach out
to you, Eve,

31:59.134 --> 32:01.049
but I didn't think
you wanted to hear from me.

32:01.093 --> 32:03.965
- Of course I did.
We all did.

32:04.009 --> 32:07.926
You were part of the family,
Levi, and you just left.

32:10.798 --> 32:12.539
- I'm sorry.

32:12.582 --> 32:14.106
After everything
that happened with Izzy,

32:14.149 --> 32:16.804
I just--

32:16.847 --> 32:18.806
I figured it'd be easier
if I wasn't around.

32:18.849 --> 32:21.113
- It wasn't.

32:24.029 --> 32:25.291
You know, a couple weeks ago,

32:25.334 --> 32:27.902
I actually thought
about calling you?

32:27.946 --> 32:29.121
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

32:29.164 --> 32:31.253
- Why?

32:31.297 --> 32:33.821
- 'Cause I missed you.

32:36.476 --> 32:38.478
I left Gavin.

32:38.521 --> 32:41.176
[tender music]

32:41.220 --> 32:43.352
That's why the kids
and I were in LA.

32:46.051 --> 32:51.621
After you left,
I really tried to make it work.

32:51.665 --> 32:52.971
I just kept waiting for the day

32:53.014 --> 32:56.148
that he would finally
be there for us again.

32:57.192 --> 33:00.456
I guess I realized it was just
never gonna happen.

33:00.500 --> 33:02.328
- Eve...

33:03.807 --> 33:06.201
Gavin was a rock for Izzy.

33:06.245 --> 33:08.334
And he's why
I'm here right now.

33:09.639 --> 33:11.511
- What do you mean?

33:11.554 --> 33:13.904
- His visions are real.

33:13.948 --> 33:15.950
Everything that he's seen
these past few years

33:15.994 --> 33:19.040
have been glimpses
of this world.

33:21.042 --> 33:22.391
The only reason
there is a rescue mission

33:22.435 --> 33:25.003
is because Gavin saw
that you were alive down here.

33:26.352 --> 33:28.615
- That's impossible.
- I thought the same thing,

33:28.658 --> 33:30.095
but it's true.

33:31.748 --> 33:34.316
And he wanted me
to give you this.

33:34.360 --> 33:41.236
♪

33:41.280 --> 33:42.759
- I don't understand.
I lost this.

33:42.803 --> 33:45.240
I lost this down here.
- I know.

33:45.284 --> 33:49.070
Gavin saw it happen.
He dug it up.

33:53.205 --> 33:57.426
I know it's hard to believe,
but it's all true.

34:03.737 --> 34:05.826
- I need a minute.

34:08.742 --> 34:10.744
- I understand.

34:13.355 --> 34:14.748
Good night, Eve.

34:16.141 --> 34:20.232
[emotional music]

34:20.275 --> 34:27.152
♪

34:27.195 --> 34:30.242
[horses snuffling,
birds chirping]

34:40.774 --> 34:43.081
- [huffs]

34:48.999 --> 34:52.655
- Gavin.
- How do you know my name?

34:52.699 --> 34:56.529
- Because I told her about you.

34:56.572 --> 35:00.098
- Dr. Nathan,
what the hell is going on?

35:03.492 --> 35:03.710
.

35:03.753 --> 35:05.407
- What are you doing here?

35:05.451 --> 35:07.061
- I could ask you
the same thing.

35:07.105 --> 35:09.629
- Levi's alive.
I found my file on your desk,

35:09.672 --> 35:12.153
saw the picture of you two
in the Mojave.

35:12.197 --> 35:13.459
I came here
looking for answers.

35:13.502 --> 35:16.201
- About?
- The other sinkholes.

35:17.027 --> 35:18.725
We know about them.
- If there's another way

35:18.768 --> 35:21.336
to get to Eve and Josh,
you need to tell us.

35:21.380 --> 35:23.991
- Sophia, we need his help.

35:24.034 --> 35:26.341
- I told you, I didn't want
to involve him in this

35:26.385 --> 35:28.126
if we didn't have to.

35:28.169 --> 35:30.345
They've been through enough.

35:30.389 --> 35:33.043
- We're out of options.
- Hey.

35:33.087 --> 35:35.394
What is she talking about?

35:35.437 --> 35:37.047
- The other sinkholes
are closed.

35:37.091 --> 35:38.745
The only way to your family
is the one at La Brea.

35:38.788 --> 35:40.181
- Well,
that's gonna be a problem,

35:40.225 --> 35:42.183
'cause Markman's not
letting anyone else down there.

35:42.227 --> 35:43.924
- Who says we need Markman?

35:46.405 --> 35:47.754
- You have another way?

35:50.974 --> 35:52.759
- Come with us.

35:57.938 --> 35:59.461
- We keep heading south,
we should be there

35:59.505 --> 36:01.333
in less than a quarter mile.

36:03.944 --> 36:06.251
- You're kidding me.
Those were Lucas' drugs?

36:06.294 --> 36:08.340
- Yeah.
So thanks for that.

36:08.383 --> 36:11.343
- Dude, at some point,
you need to man up.

36:11.386 --> 36:14.955
If he's messing with you, you
got to meet force with force.

36:14.998 --> 36:17.000
- What part of "he has a gun"
don't you understand?

36:17.044 --> 36:20.743
- Hey, Scott.
We need to have a chat, buddy.

36:20.787 --> 36:22.615
- Hey, man, listen,
I'm really sorry

36:22.658 --> 36:24.443
about what happened before,
just please don't kill me.

36:24.486 --> 36:28.534
- Why would I kill you?
You're my new best friend.

36:28.577 --> 36:30.840
- I am?
- Yeah.

36:31.841 --> 36:35.018
You're the only person
who knows where my drugs are.

36:35.062 --> 36:37.238
I got to make sure nothing
happens to you out here.

36:37.282 --> 36:40.285
So you're not leaving my side.

36:41.590 --> 36:43.810
But if you don't give 'em to me
when we get back,

36:43.853 --> 36:46.160
I will kill you.

36:46.204 --> 36:48.945
- Quid pro quo, makes sense.

36:51.600 --> 36:56.605
- Listen,
I know last night was a lot,

36:56.649 --> 36:57.998
if you want to talk about it.

37:00.827 --> 37:02.176
- When he first
had his accident,

37:02.220 --> 37:04.265
he kept trying to tell me
that this was all real,

37:04.309 --> 37:08.095
and I just--
I didn't believe him.

37:08.138 --> 37:09.575
We took him to so many doctors

37:09.618 --> 37:12.142
and none of them could
find anything wrong with him.

37:12.186 --> 37:13.535
- There's no way you could
have known it was true.

37:13.579 --> 37:15.145
Even Gavin didn't.

37:16.190 --> 37:18.845
- I know, I just want to get
home and tell him I'm sorry.

37:21.500 --> 37:26.548
- Eve, there's one more thing.

37:30.160 --> 37:32.162
Gavin knows about us.

37:32.206 --> 37:35.775
[dramatic music]

37:35.818 --> 37:38.168
- Whoa.
Guys, over here!

37:38.212 --> 37:40.170
What is that?

37:40.214 --> 37:43.173
[tense music]

37:43.217 --> 37:46.525
♪

37:46.568 --> 37:48.527
- Scott, any ideas?

37:48.570 --> 37:51.704
- I'm gonna go with
some kind of fort.

37:51.747 --> 37:55.098
I mean, there were indigenous
people during this time,

37:55.142 --> 37:56.970
but I don't think
they made structures like that.

37:58.624 --> 38:02.584
- Well, whatever it is, that's
where the signal's coming from.

38:03.759 --> 38:06.371
- Well,
then that's where we're going.

38:14.248 --> 38:16.511
- We're not here to take care
of these people.

38:16.555 --> 38:18.600
If you even think
about talking,

38:18.644 --> 38:20.907
you know what will happen.

38:20.950 --> 38:23.518
I don't think
this is a good idea.

38:23.562 --> 38:25.085
- Just give him a chance.

38:27.087 --> 38:28.741
- Please, Veronica.

38:32.397 --> 38:35.791
- I'll be right here.
If you upset her, this is over.

38:41.231 --> 38:44.452
- What does she want
to show us, a horse?

38:45.497 --> 38:47.760
[scanner beeps]

38:49.152 --> 38:50.850
- After you.

38:54.027 --> 38:56.943
[intense music]

38:56.986 --> 38:59.249
♪

38:59.293 --> 39:01.556
- This is the plane Levi flew.

39:01.600 --> 39:04.603
- With some
slight modifications.

39:04.646 --> 39:05.995
- Who are you?

39:06.039 --> 39:08.171
- Someone who wants
the same thing you do,

39:08.215 --> 39:10.130
to get to that place below.

39:11.000 --> 39:12.393
- Well, looks like you went
to a lot of trouble

39:12.437 --> 39:13.742
to make that happen.

39:13.786 --> 39:15.091
- Rebecca and I were part
of a team

39:15.135 --> 39:17.224
that investigated
the Mojave sinkhole.

39:17.267 --> 39:19.182
An exploratory crew
was sent down there,

39:19.226 --> 39:21.315
and she designed the plane
that took them.

39:21.359 --> 39:23.578
They made it through the light,

39:23.622 --> 39:26.276
but it closed
before they could come back.

39:26.320 --> 39:28.801
- So why are you hiding
out here on a ranch?

39:28.844 --> 39:29.932
- Well, when a mission
like that goes wrong,

39:29.976 --> 39:32.413
someone has
to be the scapegoat.

39:32.457 --> 39:34.110
That was me.

39:34.154 --> 39:36.548
But I promised myself
that if there was ever a chance

39:36.591 --> 39:39.202
to get back there,
I would be ready.

39:39.246 --> 39:41.683
I know why Captain Delgado's
plane failed

39:41.727 --> 39:43.859
and why it caused
those earthquakes.

39:43.903 --> 39:46.079
I also know that mine won't
have the same issues.

39:46.122 --> 39:48.821
- That's why I came here,
Gavin.

39:48.864 --> 39:50.997
I knew she was working
on her own plane.

39:51.040 --> 39:54.087
- But my pilot backed out
after Levi's plane crashed,

39:54.130 --> 39:57.786
which makes you coming here
a touch of fate.

39:59.875 --> 40:01.747
- You want me to fly?

40:03.313 --> 40:06.839
- You came here looking
for a way to save your family.

40:09.189 --> 40:10.843
This is it.

40:12.758 --> 40:19.460
- Now I know
yesterday was scary.

40:19.504 --> 40:22.768
But I promise you,
you're safe now.

40:24.509 --> 40:28.817
I want to ask you a few
questions about what you saw.

40:28.861 --> 40:35.389
But all you have to do
is shake your head yes or no.

40:35.433 --> 40:37.565
Can you do that?

40:37.609 --> 40:40.568
[tense music]

40:40.612 --> 40:43.615
♪

40:43.658 --> 40:45.181
Good.

40:46.792 --> 40:48.881
Did you see what hurt Eddie?

40:51.274 --> 40:53.320
Was it a person?

40:57.237 --> 40:58.586
Okay.

40:59.718 --> 41:03.199
Now I want you to think back

41:03.243 --> 41:05.811
and see if you can remember
what they look like.

41:08.335 --> 41:10.032
Can you do that for me?

41:13.427 --> 41:15.516
- I'm stopping this--too much.
- No, you're not.

41:15.560 --> 41:17.083
- No, no, no.
Veronica.

41:17.126 --> 41:19.694
Veronica, hang on a minute.
- Veronica, please.

41:19.738 --> 41:21.217
- What are you doing?
Let's go.

41:21.261 --> 41:22.915
- It was an old man.

41:24.569 --> 41:28.398
- You talk?
- I'll be damned.

41:29.225 --> 41:31.314
- Lilly, stop.
- He was coming toward me,

41:31.358 --> 41:33.926
but then he just left.

41:33.969 --> 41:36.276
He had something on his back.
- What was it?

41:38.321 --> 41:40.933
- A handprint.

41:40.976 --> 41:42.674
- That's enough, we're leaving.
- No, we're not done here.

41:42.717 --> 41:44.893
Ver--

41:44.937 --> 41:48.070
[suspenseful music]

41:48.114 --> 41:51.770
♪

42:01.127 --> 42:03.782
- You ready?
- Yeah, let's go.

42:05.610 --> 42:08.569
[tense music]

42:08.613 --> 42:15.184
♪

42:15.228 --> 42:18.797
- Uh, I'm not so sure
about this, guys.
